For many who witnessed the scene, it was an unbelievable incident at Onitsha, Anambra stated on Wednesday as a Bible remained unscathed after a fire completely razed not less than three cars. According to reports, the cars were parked in front of a compound when the fire started and everything inside burnt to ashes except the Bible. In a viral video that surfaced following the incident, a man could be seen rising up the Holy Bible and flipping its pages to show that it hadn’t been burnt. Most of the onlookers were seemingly amazed, praising and referencing the sovereignty of God.   Alesh raises the alarm over fake drinks in clubs     Seun Kuti knocks colleagues over Oxlade’s s3x tape     They don’t want me to see my children, Blackface cries out   - Advertisement - The incident has elicited reactions among social media users. Among the reactors are popular OAP Daddy Freeze and son of Afrobeat pioneer, Seun Kuti. Daddy Freeze, who shared a screenshot of the post on his Instagram page, wrote: “So phones and iPads that contain bibles too shouldn’t burn now, abi?” Reacting in the comment section of the post, Big Bird wrote: “The tablets and phones burn baba but the Bible app remains unscathed.”